settings.name: hard_mode
settings.description: Play the randomizer in hard mode.

settings.name: shuffle_symbols
settings.description: You will need to unlock puzzle symbols as items to be able to solve the panels that contain those symbols. If you turn this off, there will be no progression items in the game unless you turn on door shuffle.

settings.name: shuffle_lasers
settings.description: Adds laser activations as items in the multiworld pool. ***Note:** There is a visual bug that can occur with the Desert Laser. It does not affect gameplay - The Laser can still be redirected as normal, for both applications of redirection.*

settings.name: shuffle_doors
settings.description: If on, opening doors will require their respective "keys".

panels: Those keys will unlock the panels on doors.
doors_simple: The doors will magically open by themselves upon receiving the key.
doors_complex: The doors will magically open by themselves upon receiving the key.

settings.name: disable_non_randomized_puzzles
settings.description: Disable puzzles that cannot be randomized due to their environmental nature (Shadows, Monastery, and Greenhouse). The lasers for those areas will be activated as you solve optional puzzles throughout the island.

settings.name: shuffle_discarded_panels
settings.description: Add Discarded Panels into the location pool. Even disabled, solving certain Discarded Panels may still be necessary!

settings.name: shuffle_vault_boxes
settings.description: Vault Boxes will have items on them.

settings.name: shuffle_uncommon
settings.description: Adds some optional puzzles that are somewhat difficult or out of the way. Examples: Mountaintop River Shape, Tutorial Patio Floor, Theater Videos

settings.name: shuffle_postgame
settings.description: Adds locations into the pool that are guaranteed to be locked behind your goal. Use this if you don't play with forfeit on victory.

settings.name: victory_condition
settings.description: Determines which objective will send a victory signal to the AP server.

elevator: Using the final elevator will complete the game.
mountain_box_short: The objective is to unlock the Mountain (vanilla: 7 lasers).
mountain_box_long: The objective is to unlock the Challenge (vanilla: 11 lasers).

settings.name: trap_percentage
settings.description: Replaces junk items with traps, at the specified rate.

settings.name: early_secret_area
settings.description: Whether the Mountainside shortcut to the Mountain Secret Area is open from the start.

settings.name: mountain_lasers
settings.description: Sets the amount of beams required to enter the final area.

settings.name: challenge_lasers
settings.description: Sets the amount of beams required to enter the secret area through the Mountain Bottom Layer Discard.

settings.name: puzzle_skip_amount
settings.description: Adds this number of Puzzle Skips into the pool, if there is room. Puzzle Skips let you skip one panel, but cannot be used on Challenge puzzles.
